                                                                                                               Mauritius IT offer for youths
                            
	Patna, March 19 (PTI): At a time when migrant workers from Bihar workers are being attacked in states in their own country, a Mauritian firm has sent a proposal to the Bihar government seeking services of 500 ITI-trained youths.        
	Filcon Cavra Limited, a company-based in Mauritius, has sought the services of 500 youth with technical training from Bihar, conceded deputy chief minister Sushil Kumar Modi, who holds the labour portfolio.        
	The proposal which follows a visit by the Mauritius Prime Minister Navinchandra Ramgoolams visit to Bihar last month, the land of his forefathers, has been sent to the government by the companys joint managing director Philipo Sinti, Modi said.        
	Ramgoolam had affirmed that Mauritius was facing acute shortage of skilled professionals and had sought Bihar governments co-operation in meeting it.                                                                                                                                                                            
